Eric,
 
Is there a dominant American poetic that consists of first-person,
strictly referential, free-verse lyrics that are narrative, personal in
tone, make no use of space on the page, etc.? Yep, you bet. Have writing
programs caused the dominance of that poetic? I dunno. I'm willing to
consider it, but I'd also bet that were it not for the madly
proliferating MFA programs, people would still be writing the same thing,
but even worse.
 
Gwyn
