I dont think that in 1995 there can be any question regarding
Gertrude Stein's bein in the canon. Certainly that has happened long
ago. [sorry if yr seeing glitches on this page] It was happening
before she became a figure for feminist writers and critics. There is
a huge outporing of books on every level, from picture books to
decent criticism and even some scholarship. Theses galore. I will
admit that when I was teaching her in the late sixties in Montreal I
was the only one doing so at my little university, but in those days,
when the women's bookstores were finding her stuff in print again, I
spent most of my time trying to tell the store managers who HD was.
Now she too has been canonized. I would hope that HD and Stein are on
the syllabus even at Northeast Illinois State or the like. If not,
what the hell is happening down there?
