Subject:      Re: Influence query
 
it seems that most of the folks being cited as influenced by celan are people
that have translated his work.  i guess this is intuitively obvious --why wd
one undertake such a task unless one were profoundly moved by the work --but
it leads me to ask: how are each of these people --or how wd they see
themselves as --influenced by celan's work>  i know that i might cite as
influences writers whose work does not  resemble mine in the least; and i can
imagine (tho i've never translated) someone taking up a challenge to
translate a work for reasons other than "influence."  so, maybe the question
is, sort of like what i was saying about friendship the other day, what is
"influence"?  on one level it is intangible, on another level utterly
palpable.
carolyn forche, i'm glad yr on the list! your contributions are smart and
nice.--md
