Subject:      Stephen Jonas, gentleman
 
from EXCERCISES for ear (Talisman House, 1994):
 
 
VI
 
you too would yell
a plague upon
 
the heads of all
bankers
 
if I held you
by yr so
 
three hundred bil-
lion dollar debt
 
 
XV
 
youth
      of my generation
 
repaired
      to The Moon
 
thither
      did their sen-
 
timents piti-
             fully meet
 
-- broken phrases
& abbreviations grope
 
in the
      half-light
 
 
LXXXIV
 
... nor, in this common light, have we
              fared better, most
   unhappy lot
 
                    made no-
                            toriously reasonable;
chance and circumstance turns all to
           cold metallic purpose
setting no sights to move or to dance
the image, dismantled
                    all that machinery
                                       departed,
 
leaving the scene to
             maudlin abstractions,
                passions too powerful to be believed
or if believed,
               too long endured
 
***  ***
 
originally published by Andrew Crozier, The Ferry Press, London, 1968.
tod thilleman
