form an articulate and coherent pattern, but a pattern in constant process
of renewal and reorganization. The fragment becomes entire as it re-searches
memory, recovers texts, episodes, sounds and landscapes. The Bounty
interrogates the radical and violent instability of our moment, asking where
is the location of culture, where the site of self, selves, among others.
Its gaps or silences speak as determinedly, and urgently, as its singular
music."
