George, I'm posting this reply to the list in case others who may have
forgotten how to do this might want to make a note of it...
 
-> To stop mail for an indefinite amount of time, send an e-mail
message to:
 
        listserv@ubvm.cc.buffalo.edu
 
Leave the "Subject" line of the message blank. In the body of the
message, type:
 
        set poetics nomail
 
And send the message. You will receive confirmation that you have been
set to "nomail." That's all there is to it!
 
-> When you return and are ready to resume, follow the instructions
above but in the body of the message type:
 
        set poetics mail
 
Bon Voyage, George!
