One more thought--the manuscript texts are vital in thinking about the
dashes.  One of the first things you realize studying these texts (alas,
in The Manuscript Books) is that there are all sorts of dashes out
there.  Martha Nell Smith writes about these visual variations very well in
her recent book Rowing to Eden (recent, what, say 1992?).
 
