what passes for "hypertext", especially on the WWW--just cutting
up passages of linear writing and pasting 'em together w/ links
ignores the possabilities, or the _demands_, of hypertextual
grammer.  plus, the digitized vido looks *bad*...  if anyone's
planning on using this fr teaching, i'd suggest showing the
original...
